{{fq
| text   =  I'll never forget the first time I saw an Abyssal chicken... Having captured one despite its swift and cantankerous nature, I managed to soothe it with some salt pork, finding that it tolerated being held and even enjoyed scratches on its meaty body. Yet its docility was short-lived, and within moments it reverted back to its [[demonic]] nature and sought to devour my [[tiefling]] guide.
| source = [[Volo]]{{Cite card/Baldur's Gate: Descent into Avernus Dice & Miscellany||Abyssal chicken}}
| float  = right
| width  = 300px
}}

Native to the Abyss, abyssal chickens were also found on [[Avernus]]. They were spawned fully-grown in the [[Spawning Trees]]. The trees held fleshy sacks on their branches, and when mature they fell to the ground, breaking open.
